  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I register my mobile number with UAN?",
  "response": "To register your mobile number with Universal Account Number (UAN), follow these steps:\n\n1. Online Registration Process:\n- Visit the EPFO (Employees' Provident Fund Organization) portal at https://unifiedportal-mem.epfindia.gov.in/\n- Click on \"Activate UAN\"\n- Enter your UAN number\n- Enter your Aadhaar number\n- Verify details\n- Submit OTP sent to registered mobile number\n\n2. Offline Registration:\n- Visit your employer's HR department\n- Request them to update your mobile number in the UAN portal\n- Provide necessary identification documents\n\n3. Alternative Method:\n- Contact EPFO regional office\n- Submit Form 11 with updated mobile number\n- Attach necessary identity proof documents\n\nRequired Documents:\n- UAN number\n- Aadhaar card\n- PAN card\n- Proof of identity\n- Bank account details\n\nImportant Tips:\n- Ensure mobile number matches Aadhaar details\n- Keep documents ready\n- Verify information before submission\n- Contact EPFO helpline if facing issues\n\nOnce registered, you can access various EPF services through online portal and mobile app.",
